      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time, NIH) are directly linked to the hemolysis prediction objective and accepted in the regulatory literature.",
      "rationale": "Volume-averaged shear stress, scalar exposure time, and NIH are the primary QoIs. These are consistent with FDA guidance on pump hemolysis assessment and published ASME V&V 40 case studies."
